service-worker-global-scope-event-handle.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.oninstall

service-worker-global-scope-event-handle.name: onmessage
service-worker-global-scope-event-handle.summary: The ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.onmessage event of the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface is called whenever incoming messages are received.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

service-worker-global-scope-event-handle.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.onmessage

service-worker-global-scope-registration.name: registration
service-worker-global-scope-registration.summary: The registration read-only property of the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface returns a reference to the ServiceWorkerRegistration object, which represents the service worker's registration.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

service-worker-global-scope-registration.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.registration

dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-skipwaiting.name: skipWaiting
dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-skipwaiting.summary: The ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.skipWaiting() method of the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope forces the waiting service worker to become the active service worker.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-serviceworkerglobalscope-skipwaiting.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope.skipWaiting()

serviceworkerglobalscope-interface.name: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope
serviceworkerglobalscope-interface.summary: The ServiceWorkerGlobalScope interface of the ServiceWorker API represents the global execution context of a service worker.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

serviceworkerglobalscope-interface.title: ServiceWorkerGlobalScope

dom-serviceworkerregistration-active.name: active
dom-serviceworkerregistration-active.summary: The active property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface returns a service worker whose ServiceWorker.state is activating or activated. This property is initially set to null.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-serviceworkerregistration-active.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.active

dom-serviceworkerregistration-installing.name: installing
dom-serviceworkerregistration-installing.summary: The installing property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface returns a service worker whose ServiceWorker.state is installing. This property is initially set to null.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-serviceworkerregistration-installing.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.installing

dom-serviceworkerregistration-onupdatefo.name: onupdatefound
dom-serviceworkerregistration-onupdatefo.summary: The onupdatefound property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface is an EventListener property called whenever an event of type statechange is fired; it is fired any time the ServiceWorkerRegistration.installing property acquires a new service worker.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-serviceworkerregistration-onupdatefo.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.onupdatefound

dom-serviceworkerregistration-scope.name: scope
dom-serviceworkerregistration-scope.summary: The scope read-only property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface returns a unique identifier for a service worker registration. The service worker must be on the same origin as the document that registers the ServiceWorker.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-serviceworkerregistration-scope.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.scope

service-worker-registration-update.name: update
service-worker-registration-update.summary: The update() method of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface attempts to update the service worker. It fetches the worker's script URL, and if the new worker is not byte-by-byte identical to the current worker, it installs the new worker. The fetch of the worker bypasses any browser caches if the previous fetch occurred over 24 hours ago.

notes: Starting with Chrome 46, update() returns a promise that resolves with 'undefined' if the operation completed successfully or there was no update, and rejects if update failed. If the new worker ran but installation failed, the promise still resolves. Formerly, it raised an exception.
Before Chrome 48, this method always bypassed the browser cache. Starting with Chrome 48, it only bypasses the cache when the previous service worker check was more than twenty-four hours ago.

navigator-service-worker-waiting.name: waiting
navigator-service-worker-waiting.summary: The waiting property of the ServiceWorkerRegistration interface returns a service worker whose ServiceWorker.state is installed. This property is initially set to null.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

navigator-service-worker-waiting.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration.waiting

serviceworkerregistration.name: ServiceWorkerRegistration
serviceworkerregistration.summary: The ServiceWorkerRegistration interface of the Service Worker API represents the service worker registration. You register a service worker to control one or more pages that share the same origin.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

serviceworkerregistration.title: ServiceWorkerRegistration

dom-windowclient-focus.name: focus
dom-windowclient-focus.summary: The focus() method of the WindowClient interface gives user input focus to the current client and returns a Promise that resolves to the existing WindowClient.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-windowclient-focus.title: WindowClient.focus()

dom-windowclient-focused.name: focused
dom-windowclient-focused.summary: The focused read-only property of the WindowClient interface is a Boolean that indicates whether the current client has focus.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-windowclient-focused.title: WindowClient.focused

dom-windowclient-navigate.name: navigate
dom-windowclient-navigate.summary: The navigate() method of the WindowClient interface loads a specified URL into a controlled client page then returns a Promise that resolves to the existing WindowClient.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-windowclient-navigate.title: WindowClient.navigate()

dom-windowclient-visibilitystate.name: visibilityState
dom-windowclient-visibilitystate.summary: The visibilityState read-only property of the WindowClient interface indicates the visibility of the current client. This value can be one of "hidden", "visible", or "prerender".

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

dom-windowclient-visibilitystate.title: WindowClient.visibilityState

windowclient.name: WindowClient
windowclient.summary: The WindowClient interface of the ServiceWorker API represents the scope of a service worker client that is a document in a browsing context, controlled by an active worker. The service worker client independently selects and uses a service worker for its own loading and sub-resources.

firefox.notes: Service workers (and Push) have been disabled in the Firefox 45 and 52 Extended Support Releases (ESR).

windowclient.title: WindowClient

self-caches.name: caches
self-caches.summary: The caches read-only property of the WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope interface returns the CacheStorage object associated with the current context. This object enables functionality such as storing assets for offline use, and generating custom responses to requests.

firefox.notes: caches now defined on WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope mixin.

self-caches.title: WindowOrWorkerGlobalScope.caches
